Subject: RE: Shift4/FDR/CardConnect Relationship

No problem. See responses to your questions.

   1   The meetings are designed to discuss IT initiatives and other technology or product collaborations.
   2   We have no plans to move volume. We will continue to look for ways to try and send

additional volume as we did with the convenience store chain referenced in the email below which was the last program in the pipeline.
3. We have a very good relationship with Bob and his leadership team and would certainly
inform them prior to any such change. We are unaware of any CardConnect resources working
on a project to move processing from CardConnect to another platform. CardConnect also uses
other third party processors for certain services in order to meet the needs of their channel
partners and merchants.
4. Yes. We did discuss the Monica Stone affair. Jared said that everyone at Shift4 feels terrible
about this, is committed to fixing it and making sure it can never happen again. Jared said
there are text messages between him and Monica that would confirm his account of events
and Shift4 will use the legal system, to the full extent possible, to bring an end to this type of
inappropriate behavior.

Thanks,

Jared
